The Speaker of the Kogi State House of Assembly, Rt. Hon. Matthew Kolawole, yesterday, said the 6th state assembly passed 46 bills over the last four years. Hon. Kolawole disclosed this in his valedictory speech to mark the end of the 6th Kogi State House of Assembly. He said a total of 50 bills were considered of which 46 were successfully passed while four others were undergoing processes at different committee stages. Kolawole said, “Actions were suspended on others and sent back to the Ministry of Justice for re-drafting, while one was rejected and withdrawn by the sponsor for lack of merit. “It is also worthy to intimate you that a total of 144 substantive motions have been tabled before the House, while a total of 82 resolutions emanating from both substantive and subsidiary motions have been passed.” Kogi Judiciary asks court to nullify assembly's resolution on CJ's removal Reps treated 327 bills in 6 months  - Gbajabiamila Kidnapped Kogi assembly speaker's brother, three others released Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin